<br>
As she just settle down painfully into the chair, a vaguely familiar tier'dal appeared in the doorway. As the dark elf spoke, Zindella wrapped bandages around her wounds, listening intently upon any malcontent that may come from the speaker. Zindella stood up when the tier'dal spoke, ready to question on to why the dark one had taken a fancy unto the circle. But before she could speak, Dalnin leaped into action pouncing upon the tier'dal with a ferocity she had never seen from her sister before.<br>
<br>
